Name: searchpartition-name
Type: STRING
Default-Value: NULL
Last-Modified: 3.1.4
For-Documentation-Only: 1

The pathname where to store the xapian search indexes of *searchtier* for
mailboxes of partition *name*. This must be configured for the
:imapdconf:`defaultsearchtier` and any additional search tier (see
:cyrusman:`squatter(8)` for details).

For example: if :imapdconf:`defaultpartition` is defined as part1 and
:imapdconf:`defaultsearchtier` as tier1 then the configuration must contain
an entry *tier1searchpartition-part1* that defines the path where to store
this tier1's search index for the part1 partition.

This option MUST be specified for xapian search.
